author: Jason Brennan
title: TV | Live UEFA Champions League - Manchester United vs CSKA Moscow
text: Manchester United travel to Moscow as they take on CSKA in this 7.45pm kick-off. Louis Van Gaal's men have had a mixed start to their first season back in this competition, with an opening-week defeat by PSV Eindhoven followed by a 2-1 victory over VfL Wolfsburg last time out. It's not quite make or break time just yet, but a win here would ease the pressure significantly as we hit the halfway mark in the group stages. CSKA won't be pushovers though, having gone unbeaten in their first 12 league games, the currently sit at first place in the Russian Premier League.
